<P>
   FRESHMEN-PARENTS (Madison, Wis.) _ In a scene that has been
repeated hundreds of times on dozens of campuses this summer,
administrators have been gathering the parents of incoming freshmen
to gird them for the journey on which they and their families are
about to embark. While orientations for the freshmen have been
fixtures at colleges for more than a decade, the systematic
immersion of parents is recent. The purpose is plain: to enlist
parents as coaches to prod their students, and to address parents'
own emotions as they prepare to break away from their companions of
the last 18 years. By Jacques Steinberg. 1,700 words.
