<P>
   Sports stories in sight at this hour from The New York Times
News Service for use in papers of Sunday, Aug. 22:
</P>
<P>
   BBN-CHASS-COLUMN (Undated) _ The National League is faced with a
mathematical impossibility: Four into three won't go. The Mets,
Braves, Astros and Reds are competing for three playoff spots. One
of them won't make it, even though they all could have better
records than the Arizona Diamondbacks, the presumptive winner of
the NL West. By Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   LIPSYTE-COLUMN (Undated) _ Those archangels of the arena,
Michael, John, Wayne and Steffi, flew away this year, and I hardly
thought about them. All four were driven, hard-working
perfectionists who gave us our money's worth. Yet none of them
quite grabbed at our hearts or elbowed our ribs. They worked so
hard, they didn't seem to be having fun. By Robert Lipsyte.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-DROPOUT (New York) _ Four years ago, George Carrion was one
of the best high school baseball prospects to come out of New York
in 20 years. After one season at a Texas junior college, the Texas
Rangers signed him to a contract with a $700,000 bonus to play in
their minor-league system. Yet last summer, Carrion abruptly quit.
He drove home to Yonkers and has been, in his words, ``just hanging
out with buddies.'' Carrion sleeps till noon most days, goes to
nightclubs on weekends and plays rec-league softball for a
half-dozen teams around the Bronx. His mother, Margie Carrion, said
recently, ``Not a day goes by when I don't want to strangle that
kid.'' By Alan Schwarz.
</P>
<P>
   RUN-CHAMPIONSHIPS (Seville, Spain) _ First day of competition at
the World Track Championships.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-METS-CARDS (New York) _ St. Louis at New York. By Judy
Battista.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKS-TWINS (Minneapolis) _ New York at Minnesota. By Buster
Olney.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Pro football notebook. By Mike Freeman.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Major-league baseball notebook. By
Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   RAC-SARATOGA (Saratoga, N.Y.) _ The Alabama Stakes, featuring
Silverbulletday. By Joe Durso.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-RYDER-CUP (Undated) _ The heated debate concerning Ryder Cup
revenue has done little to diminish interest in next month's
biennial event. If anything, the squabble gave the Ryder Cup more
publicity, even if it wasn't the kind of publicity sought by the
PGA and the players. By Clifton Brown.
</P>
<P>
   BIKE-ARMSTRONG (Mount Snow, Vt.) _ Feature on Lance Armstrong at
the mountain bike races. By Frank Litsky.
</P>
