   FBC-TECH-DEFENSE _ ATLANTA _Georgia Tech coach George O'Leary's
defensive staff is nearly all new this season. That's quite a
turnover for a program on the rise, but the Jackets allowed an
average of around 400 yards a game last season. If Tech is to win
an ACC title, Dave Sollazzo (defensive tackles), Paul Ferraro
(defensive backs) and Danny Crossman (defensive ends/special
teams), along with new defensive coordinator, Ted Roof, will have
to deliver. (Clemons, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
