   FBC-TARHEELS _ The Road to College Football travels to North
Carolina, which is still young and inexperienced but has potential
to be very good in the future. (Arey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GIRLPLAYER _ COCHRAN, GA. _ Even on a team that started
practice with 152 football hopefuls of all sizes and shapes, one
player stands out at Middle Georgia College. The new placekicker is
the one with the ponytail, a leggy photo in Atlanta Magazine and,
temporarily, a whole dorm to herself. At Middle Georgia, the
football team is co-ed, but not student housing, meaning freshman
Tony Butler of Riverdale High School as had the girl's dorm to
herself. That changes Monday, when classes begin at Middle Georgia,
a junior college of 2,000 students about 40 miles southeast of
Macon. Next Saturday, Butler willmake her college debut when the
Warriors _ ranked No. 18 in the preseason national poll despite
only nine returning players _ open the season at Kilgore, Texas.
(Curtright, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 27. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   w/FBC-MIDDLEGA _ COCHRAN, GA. _ Despite a budget that is a
fraction of what a big-time college would spend, Middle Georgia has
won 40 games, been ranked as high as No. 2 nationally and gone to
three bowl games since resuming football in 1994. But more
importantly, it has sent more than 80 player to four-year colleges.
(Curtright, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
