Scores of people in Oakland, like Francis Torrence, right, line up
daily to catch a ride to San Francisco. Passengers mill about until
drivers, whom they do not know but who want to save the $2 San
Francisco-Oakland Bay Bridge toll and use the commuter lane, pick
them up. An unspoken etiquette has evolved among repeat carpoolers.
(Peter Dasilva/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) SAN FRANCISCO -- Aug. 21, 1999 --
SILICON-VALLEY-TRAFFIC-1, 8-21 -- As Northern California's economy
