<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN </SLUG>
 
McCULLOUGH IMPRESSIVE AMID ALL THE PENALTIES 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVINE, Calif. _ It's a new season, but USC's first official
scrimmage Saturday proved the Trojans still have a nagging problem
from last year: penalties.
</P>
<P>
   During Saturday's 94-play scrimmage at UC Irvine, the Trojans
were penalized 15 times.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's something that just plagued us,'' USC quarterback Carson
Palmer said. ``I think it had to do with being the first scrimmage.
It's the first time we had a big crowd and a game situation.''
</P>
<P>
   It was reminiscent of last season, when USC was penalized 126
times for 1,119 yards in 13 games.
</P>
<P>
   ``It just killed us. It really cost us a game or two last
year,'' USC coach Paul Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   You might think Hackett would be distressed over the penalties,
but he was fairly relaxed when assessing the number of mistakes
made.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're a very spirited and emotional bunch,'' Hackett said.
``How much was necessary and how much was over-zealousness? That's
why we have the tape.''
</P>
<P>
   As for scrimmage highlights, freshman tailback Sultan McCullough
gained 88 yards in 29 carries and scored on 1- and 2-yard runs.
</P>
<P>
   McCullough was given so many carries because starter Chad Morton
played sparingly in order to rest his hamstring, while Frank Strong
(bruised thigh) and Malaefou MacKenzie (hamstring) did not play.
</P>
<P>
   ``I really don't care (about the carries),'' McCullough said.
``I was just trying to do my thing. I'm just trying to get in
shape.''
</P>
<P>
   McCullough strained his hamstring at the NCAA Track
Championships in June. He is now one of several candidates to
replace Petros Papadakis as USC's No.2 tailback, after Papadakis
broke his foot in Friday's practice.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not scared. I'll do whatever I've got to do,'' McCullough
said. ``I can get to the end zone.''
</P>
<P>
   Palmer completed 11 of 15 passes for 135 yards, including a
65-yard scoring pass to R. Jay Soward. Mike Van Raaphorst completed
6 of 7 passes for 69 yards while John Fox completed 6 of 10 for 54
yards, including a 28-yard touchdown to freshman tight end Chad
Cook.
</P>
<P>
   Kicker David Bell missed 51- and 47-yard field-goal attempts.
</P>
<P>
   Surprise performance: True freshman safety Troy Polamalu was a
defensive star with eight tackles, two forced fumbles and 14-yard
touchdown run after stripping the ball from Jabari Jackson.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't want to redshirt at all,'' Polamalu said. ``I hope I
can play. I don't really care where the coaches put me.''
</P>
<P>
   Hackett said Polamalu, the nephew of former USC fullback Kennedy
Pola, was ``outstanding'' but that no decisions have been made on a
redshirt season.
</P>
<P>
   Sore arm: Palmer skipped Saturday morning's practice to rest his
arm, which has been sore because he and Van Raaphorst are USC's
only scholarship quarterbacks.
</P>
<P>
   ``My arm's been worn out,'' Palmer said.
</P>
<P>
   Injury update: Defensive tackle Bernard Riley and offensive
lineman Trevor Roberts sprained their ankles and will be out at
least a week.
</P>
<P>
   Offensive tackle Brent McCaffrey left the scrimmage early with
sore ribs, while wide receiver Windrell Hayes had a slightly
sprained ankle. Missing the scrimmage entirely was wide receiver
Marcell Allmond (hamstring).
</P>
<P>
   Hackett said none of those injuries were serious. Papadakis will
probably have foot surgery by midweek. Hackett said there is a
chance USC would appeal to the NCAA for a sixth year of eligibility
for Papadakis.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
